Nació en Saigón y más adelante emigró a los Estados Unidos. Allí, Yenn se suscitó en el Ada, Minnesota y luego se trasladó al sur de California. Ella apareció en Asia desde el año 2000, publicando un DVD sobre los espectáculos musicales, generando muchas obras maestras coreográficas y musicales. Yenn grabado y publicado diez discos en su lengua materna a través de su anterior sello. Con una serie de CD más vendidos y DVD, además ayudó introduciendo a la escena pop internacional, Yenn ha desarrollado devotos seguidores de toda Europa, Asia y Australia, con sus fascinantes actuaciones de alta energía. Ella es bien conocida con famosas canciones como "Sólo para Adultos Ceremonia", "Voi Anh, Dem No," Voulez Vous "," Dem Buon Nhu Thanh Ca "y" Co Nhung Chuyen Tinh Khong La Tranvía Nam ". Ella ha lanzado su primer single titulado EE.UU. "So Good To Be Wrong" junto a "Show Me Your Heaven".

Dạ Nhật Yến (born October 12), professionally known as Yenn, is a Vietnamese American singer and dancer. She was born in Saigon, and later immigrated to the United States. There, Yenn was raised in Ada, Minnesota and later moved to Southern California. She appeared in Asia Entertainment since 2000 DVD musical shows, generating many choreographical and musical masterpieces. Yenn recorded and released ten albums in her native language through her former label. With a series of best-selling CDs and DVDs helped introduced her to the international pop scene, Yenn developed a devoted following throughout Europe, Asia and Australia with her captivating high-energy performances. She is well known for songs such as "Adult Ceremony," "Voi Anh Dem Nay," "Voulez Vous", "Dem Buon Nhu Thanh Ca," and "Co Nhung Chuyen Tinh Khong La Tram Nam." She has released her first US single entitled "So Good to be Wrong" along with "Show Me Your Heaven."
